"use strict";(self.webpackChunkknowledge=self.webpackChunkknowledge||[]).push([[3244],{8157:(e,p,t)=>{t.r(p),t.d(p,{data:()=>o});const o={key:"v-20d59b31",path:"/language/the-100/4-9.html",title:"",lang:"zh-CN",frontmatter:{},excerpt:"",headers:[],filePathRelative:"language/the-100/4-9.md",git:{updatedTime:163878296e4,contributors:[{name:"黎聪",email:"licong23@xdf.cn",commits:1}]}}},5517:(e,p,t)=>{t.r(p),t.d(p,{default:()=>a});const o=(0,t(6252).uE)("<p>Previously on &quot;The 100&quot;...</p><p>The death wave will be here in 10 days.</p><p>What I found was a fallout shelter,</p><p>salvation lies within.</p><p>The radiation doesn&#39;t care</p><p>if you&#39;re Trikru or Azgeda.</p><p>Azgeda will never see the inside.</p><p>What if we share it?</p><p>I can live with that.</p><p>When the time comes to close the door,</p><p>Azgeda will see that it&#39;s done.</p><p>I&#39;ll take you home.</p><p>Raven, you need to slow down.</p><p>Your brain scan showed evidence of a stroke.</p><p>The door is stuck.</p><p>Raven, it could kill you.</p><p>We can&#39;t create Nightblood</p><p>unless we go to space,</p><p>but Luna can.</p><p>We can inject ourselves with her bone marrow.</p><p>Then we become Nightbloods.</p><p>I bear it so they don&#39;t have to.</p><p>One day, they will thank you</p><p>for what you&#39;re doing here.</p><p>What if it doesn&#39;t work?</p><p>Then we die,</p><p>knowing we did everything we could</p><p>to save our people.</p><p>I got it.</p><p>It&#39;s heavy.</p><p>Uhh.</p><p>This is why they left us behind?</p><p>To scavenge tech?</p><p>Hey, we talked about this.</p><p>We didn&#39;t get left behind.</p><p>They&#39;re coming back.</p><p>Forgive me if I don&#39;t believe</p><p>what your people say anymore.</p><p>Murphy&#39;s actually right.</p><p>Don&#39;t worry, they might ditch him,</p><p>but I&#39;m too awesome to leave behind.</p><ul><li>There you go.</li><li>Congratulations, Emori.</li></ul><p>You get to live</p><p>in a hole in the ground for 5 years.</p><p>Thanks for playing.</p><p>Come on. At least we get to live.</p><p>Said the cockroach to the Raven.</p><p>Systems check complete.</p><p>What?</p><p>Orbital launch systems online.</p><p>You don&#39;t hear that?</p><p>Emori, get the seizure kit now.</p><p>Abby left it in the office.</p><p>No.</p><p>No, it&#39;s--it&#39;s OK.</p><p>It&#39;s OK. I&#39;m fine.</p><p>Put that stuff with the gear for the last run.</p><p>I&#39;ll start on the processors.</p><p>No, no, no, no. No coding, all right?</p><p>Luna&#39;s not here to whisper in your ear</p><p>and I&#39;d rather not have your brain</p><p>melt on my watch.</p><p>I&#39;m not coding. I&#39;m unhooking.</p><p>Now do what I said.</p><p>Then you can take a break.</p><p>I&#39;ll need some time with this.</p><p>Sure thing.</p><p>Come on.</p><p>What&#39;s the matter now?</p><p>If she can&#39;t use her brain,</p><p>why do they need her?</p><p>Initiating ground launch sequencer now.</p><p>Uhh.</p><p>Raven.</p><p>Becca?</p><p>You can tell me that it&#39;s none of my business,</p><p>but why live in a hole in the ground</p><p>when you have a perfectly good rocket?</p><p>Are you tilling the soil or stabbing it?</p><p>You know this is dumb, right?</p><p>We&#39;ll all be dead before anything grows.</p><p>The earth survived Praimfaya once.</p><p>It will again.</p><p>We do this for those who come after us.</p><p>Let me show you.</p><p>Ilian.</p><p>Head down. Say nothing.</p><p>My people are wary of strangers.</p><p>Ankara.</p><p>War.</p><p>You didn&#39;t tell me you were a warrior.</p><p>Not much point in fighting at the end of the world.</p><p>Yeah!</p><p>There is an underground aquifer</p><p>with a filtration system that is still operational.</p><p>Some of the water will go to the hydroponic farm.</p><p>Isn&#39;t that right, Mr. Green?</p><p>Most beautiful thing I&#39;ve ever seen.</p><p>Almost.</p><p>It won&#39;t be easy.</p><p>There will be plenty of hard work to go around.</p><p>But together we have struggled.</p><p>And together we will rise.</p><p>Pack your things. Just what you can carry.</p><p>We leave at first light.</p><p>Thank you. Thank you.</p><ul><li>You&#39;re a hero, Monty.</li><li>Stop.</li></ul><p>Go back.</p><p>I&#39;ll be there as soon as we</p><p>finish with the armory.</p><p>Jaha was right.</p><p>Got a lot of gear to pack.</p><p>Sure you&#39;re not too hung over?</p><p>You judging me, Monty?</p><p>A little.</p><p>There was no hope. Now there&#39;s hope.</p><p>Let&#39;s go.</p><p>Jasper...</p><p>You&#39;re gonna love it.</p><p>Give him a minute.</p><p>They&#39;ll figure it out when we take the still.</p><p>We don&#39;t need it.</p><p>There&#39;s one in the bunker.</p><p>My little boy&#39;s all grown up.</p><p>So what?</p><p>We hole up in a bunker now?</p><p>Do everything Jaha says?</p><p>Back to life on the ark?</p><p>Now that is just crazy talk.</p><p>Since when do we listen to what Jaha says?</p><p>The tunnel&#39;s just through those woods.</p><p>How long are you staying?</p><p>Quick turnaround. If you forgot anything</p><p>at the lab, let me know.</p><p>Or I could keep you company.</p><p>Right.</p><p>Clarke, can I talk to you for a second?</p><p>I&#39;ll catch up.</p><p>What&#39;s wrong?</p><p>There&#39;s something I didn&#39;t tell you.</p><p>Indra was with them when they found the bunker.</p><p>Trikru knows?</p><p>Yes. We made a deal with them</p><p>to share the space.</p><p>What about our deal with Roan?</p><p>Trikru would rather go to war</p><p>than live with Azgeda.</p><p>Mom, Roan is my friend.</p><p>Our ally.</p><p>Not anymore.</p><p>Why didn&#39;t you tell me this before?</p><p>They&#39;re gonna kill him.</p><p>No, Clarke,</p><p>not if he comes peacefully.</p><p>We will make room for one.</p><p>Indra agreed.</p><p>Uh!</p><p>Gentlemen.</p><p>It&#39;s good to see you.</p><p>Just--wait here.</p><p>Where are the guards?</p><p>Our people aren&#39;t back from Arkadia yet.</p><ul><li>Kane, don&#39;t. Roan!</li><li>Look. Wait.</li></ul><p>Trikru.</p><p>What is this?</p><p>There doesn&#39;t have to be any violence.</p><p>Wait, stop!</p><p>Welcome back to Polis, my king.</p><p>I said, explain.</p><p>Skaikru allied with Trikru</p><p>to take the temple.</p><p>They gave up the tower to do it.</p><p>Strategically, that made no sense,</p><p>so I put our people at the temple doors.</p><p>Good thing I did.</p><p>You did well, Echo.</p><p>Move the rest of our army to the temple doors.</p><p>No one gets in or out.</p><p>Go.</p><p>How long have you known?</p><p>I just found out.</p><p>Thanks for trying to warn me.</p><p>This doesn&#39;t have to turn into a war.</p><p>It&#39;s already a war.</p><p>Only if you fight it.</p><p>Your people betrayed me, Clarke.</p><p>What would you have me do?</p><p>Live?</p><p>The radiation&#39;s gonna be here</p><p>in 6 days.</p><p>You were willing to share the bunker with us.</p><p>Why not share it with Trikru, too?</p><p>I suppose Kane tried to get Indra to do that</p><p>before agreeing to let them assassinate me.</p><p>Believe it or not,</p><p>Kane was trying to save your life.</p><p>Mine, maybe. Not my people&#39;s.</p><p>That was before you surrounded the temple.</p><p>Look, now no one can get in to survive</p><p>unless you allow it.</p><p>Indra will have no choice but to talk.</p><p>Fine. We&#39;ll talk.</p><p>But I&#39;m holding your people.</p><p>My chancellor needs to be at that meeting, Roan.</p><p>Your chancellor&#39;s lucky he still has his head.</p><p>Besides, if anyone can convince</p><p>mortal enemies to move in together, it&#39;s you.</p><p>I&#39;ll call for the summit.</p><p>All I can think about is there&#39;s a war going on</p><p>and I&#39;m not in it.</p><p>No war will stop Praimfaya.</p><p>At least it would be a warrior&#39;s death.</p><p>Better than melting.</p><p>My people have a saying:</p><p>Reincarnation?</p><p>You believe in that?</p><p>The crops, they die in winter</p><p>and then return in spring.</p><p>Most people don&#39;t know when their winter will come,</p><p>but we do.</p><p>And that&#39;s a gift.</p><p>Why waste it in fighting?</p><p>You&#39;re not packed.</p><p>I tried.</p><p>Talk to me, Harper.</p><p>Just tired of fighting, Monty.</p><p>I know.</p><p>We all are.</p><p>But in that bunker, we&#39;ll be safe.</p><p>Every time we think that, something bad happens.</p><p>So what then? Stay here and die?</p><p>Spend your last days wasted?</p><p>That seems to be a popular choice</p><p>with the people I care about.</p><ul><li>Monty, I--</li><li>it&#39;ll be light out soon.</li></ul><p>That bunker gives us a chance for a future.</p><p>I hope you&#39;ll change your mind.</p><p>I won&#39;t.</p><p>I was, um--I was thinking about Louis.</p><p>About how you blame yourself for his death</p><p>because you didn&#39;t stop to save him</p><p>from the black rain.</p><p>You didn&#39;t do that because you were</p><p>a coward, Harper.</p><p>You did that because you wanted to live.</p><p>It&#39;s called survival instinct.</p><p>This is the first time</p><p>I ever thought you were a coward.</p><p>Aren&#39;t you going the wrong way?</p><p>Come to say good-bye?</p><p>Hell no.</p><p>Hey.</p><p>I thought I made it clear.</p><p>We need everyone packed</p><p>and ready to go by--</p><p>first light.</p><p>We&#39;ll get right on it.</p><p>Good.</p><p>We&#39;re talking about the future of the human race</p><p>here, Mr. Jordan.</p><p>Participation is not optional.</p><p>They&#39;re gonna make us go with them.</p><p>It&#39;s a test.</p><p>How bad do we want this?</p><p>There is a way out now.</p><p>When this party started, that wasn&#39;t true.</p><p>Make no mistake-- you choose to stay</p><p>and you&#39;re choosing death.</p><p>If that&#39;s your decision, I&#39;m with you all the way.</p><p>If not, there&#39;s the door.</p><p>No one here will judge you if you leave.</p><p>OK, then.</p><p>I guess we have nothing to lose.</p><p>You can&#39;t ignore me forever, Raven.</p><p>I mean, I guess you could try,</p><p>but we&#39;re the same, you and I,</p><p>and I know the truth.</p><p>You don&#39;t want to live in a bunker,</p><p>and you don&#39;t want to be the good little soldier,</p><p>always doing what Clarke tells you to do.</p><p>I know what you do want.</p><p>Stop. Stop!</p><p>God, you&#39;re not-- you&#39;re not real.</p><p>You&#39;re just--</p><p>that doesn&#39;t mean that I&#39;m not right.</p><p>What the hell do you want from me?</p><p>I want to help you.</p><p>Your time is running out.</p><p>And I&#39;m not talking about the radiation.</p><p>I&#39;m talking about your brain.</p><p>You need to ask yourself--</p><p>how are you gonna go out?</p><p>Down here?</p><p>Miserable? In pain?</p><p>Or up there? Free? Floating?</p><p>I&#39;ve run all the simulations.</p><p>There&#39;s not enough fuel to get back.</p><p>Who said anything about getting back?</p><p>Your friends are taken care of.</p><p>They don&#39;t need you to keep them alive</p><p>in the bunker.</p><p>But you will need them</p><p>if you go there.</p><p>The computer code is destroying your neurons</p><p>at an advanced rate.</p><p>Soon you&#39;re not gonna know how to tie</p><p>your own shoes,</p><p>let alone how to convert</p><p>a launch entry suit into something</p><p>that you can spacewalk in.</p><p>You can help me spacewalk?</p><p>If you&#39;re gonna go out,</p><p>might as well go out with a view.</p><p>Come on, come back.</p><p>I&#39;m good to go again.</p><p>Your friend Miller should be back by now.</p><p>They&#39;re not coming back, John.</p><p>So we go to Polis ourselves.</p><p>The boat&#39;s on the wrong side of the water.</p><p>We&#39;ll never make it.</p><p>Then I guess we ride out the storm</p><p>in the lighthouse bunker.</p><p>For 5 years?</p><p>We&#39;ll starve.</p><p>Who needs food when you have</p><p>love, right?</p><p>We were searched outside.</p><p>If I&#39;m not back in an hour,</p><p>my army will attack.</p><p>You must be gaia.</p><ul><li>I&#39;m--</li><li>I know who you are...</li></ul><p>Wanheda.</p><p>You helped my people find the bunker.</p><p>Thank you for that.</p><p>And you gave the flame</p><p>to an unworthy king, who saw it destroyed.</p><p>I am not as grateful.</p><p>Let&#39;s see what all the fuss is about.</p><p>After you, Wanheda.</p><p>All my enemies in one place.</p><p>Who are they?</p><p>The war chiefs of the Trikru alliance.</p><p>She was supposed to be alone.</p><p>What fun would that be?</p><p>You murdered our people.</p><p>You burned our villages.</p><p>Yet you have the nerve to come here</p><p>in the name of peace.</p><p>Not peace. Survival.</p><p>You tried to take this bunker for yourself,</p><p>yet here I am, willing to talk.</p><p>The Trikru alliance holds the temple.</p><p>Of course you&#39;re willing to talk.</p><p>And the Azgeda alliance</p><p>surrounds it.</p><p>None of your people will get inside</p><p>unless we come to terms.</p><p>This war is inevitable.</p><p>The only reason it hasn&#39;t happened before now</p><p>is that Lexa commanded it.</p><p>The only thing that&#39;s inevitable is Praimfaya.</p><p>In 6 days,</p><p>anyone who is not in this bunker will be dead.</p><p>Then we should get to it.</p><p>Roan.</p><p>We talked.</p><p>Now we fight.</p><p>No.</p><p>There is room for 1,200 people in here.</p><p>We could share it equally.</p><p>All of the clans can survive.</p><p>That&#39;s what Lexa would have wanted.</p><p>You&#39;re right. She would have.</p><p>And if she were here, the clans</p><p>might actually have obeyed her.</p><p>But seeing that there&#39;s no commander to rule us...</p><p>War it is.</p><p>What are you doing?</p><p>I know you have the flame.</p><p>I know Octavia gave it to you.</p><p>I think you should leave, Clarke.</p><p>I can&#39;t let them fight a war over</p><p>the one thing that can save us.</p><p>Not even Wanheda can stop the clans</p><p>from killing each other.</p><p>No. But a commander could.</p><p>Of course a commander could.</p><p>Unfortunately, we need a Natblida for that.</p><p>Make me the commander.</p><p>Ahh. It&#39;s jammed.</p><p>Same as the others.</p><p>But this is the door to blow.</p><p>How many gas canisters do we have?</p><p>You can&#39;t be serious.</p><p>In mount weather, we beat the gas</p><p>by using water.</p><p>Jasper will be ready for that.</p><p>Just slow down. Let me talk to them.</p><p>Bellamy, we have over 400 people</p><p>ready to march.</p><p>Gun.</p><p>Harper&#39;s.</p><p>How many more of them are armed?</p><p>I don&#39;t know. A few.</p><p>&quot;DNR&quot;?</p><p>Do not resuscitate.</p><p>Jasper, put down the gun.</p><p>Open the door.</p><p>We&#39;re not coming out.</p><p>This is insane.</p><p>Are you really willing to die,</p><p>when there&#39;s a way to live?</p><p>Are they?</p><p>That&#39;s just it. We don&#39;t think</p><p>it&#39;s a way to live.</p><p>Just go. Please.</p><p>We&#39;re wasting time. Set the charge.</p><p>You can go to guns.</p><p>Do not fire unless fired upon.</p><p>Is that clear?</p><p>No. OK, just-- just wait.</p><p>Jasper, people will get hurt.</p><p>I know you care about that.</p><p>If you don&#39;t want anyone to get hurt,</p><p>don&#39;t open the door.</p><p>We&#39;re all set. We should clear the hall.</p><p>Mr. Jordan,</p><p>I will not leave children here to die.</p><p>You sent them down to die.</p><p>The difference now</p><p>is that they have a choice.</p><p>And so do you.</p><p>What are you talking about?</p><p>This is what they want.</p><p>They&#39;re wasted. They don&#39;t know what they want.</p><p>Stand down.</p><p>Get ready to move out.</p><ul><li>Yes, sir.</li><li>What?</li></ul><p>No. You can&#39;t.</p><p>I&#39;m sorry, son. Bellamy is right.</p><p>We can&#39;t save them if they don&#39;t</p><p>want to be saved.</p><p>If Octavia was in there,</p><p>would you let her stay?</p><p>If Octavia was in there...</p><p>At least I&#39;d get to say good-bye.</p><p>That&#39;s it, isn&#39;t it?</p><p>Skairipa.</p><p>I saw you in Polis.</p><p>You murdered my friend Terro.</p><p>Cut off his head.</p><p>I&#39;m not that person anymore.</p><p>Uhh!</p><p>Please.</p><p>You don&#39;t want to do this.</p><p>Uhh!</p><p>Trust me. Just walk away.</p><p>Aah! Uhh!</p><p>Aah! Aah!</p><p>This is who I am.</p><p>Once reinforcements arrive, we can edge in west</p><p>to the temple quarter.</p><p>No. There&#39;s no time.</p><p>We need to squeeze out Boudalankru first.</p><p>Here and here.</p><p>The ascension call.</p><p>The flame was destroyed.</p><p>How is this possible?</p><p>You said you saw it.</p><p>It was shattered.</p><p>I saw what they wanted me to see.</p><p>A new commander is bad for us, Roan.</p><p>But we control the tower.</p><p>Let me stop this ascension,</p><p>at least until we know who the Natblida is.</p><p>I know who it is.</p><p>Are you presiding?</p><p>Yes.</p><p>The flame chose me as its protector.</p><p>Our scouts honor that.</p><p>Did one of them find a Natblida?</p><p>Obviously.</p><p>What clan are they from?</p><p>This is highly unusual, gaia.</p><p>There was no conclave.</p><p>There are questions to be answered.</p><p>What is this? Wanheda is no Natblida!</p><p>Ascende...</p><p>Lies upon lies.</p><p>Get out of this sacred circle.</p><p>There&#39;s nothing sacred about any of this.</p><p>Wanheda is making a mockery of our faith.</p><p>I&#39;m trying to save us, your highness.</p><p>You know that.</p><p>Because you think we&#39;re savages</p><p>in need of saving?</p><p>Praimfaya is almost here.</p><p>Then let&#39;s not waste any more time.</p><p>Bring in the healer!</p><p>What are you doing?</p><p>We don&#39;t know if this works.</p><p>The flame could kill you.</p><p>I have no choice.</p><p>Tell them, healer.</p><p>Go on, tell them all</p><p>how it is your daughter</p><p>became a Natblida.</p><p>Through science.</p><p>You made her a Nightblood?</p><p>Yes.</p><p>If anyone can be a Natblida,</p><p>if anyone can take the flame,</p><p>then we can no longer trust the blood.</p><p>What we can still trust is the sword.</p><p>We&#39;ve delayed this war long enough.</p><p>Wait.</p><p>Wanheda is right about one thing.</p><p>Fighting a war is a bad way to decide</p><p>who gets to survive.</p><p>You summoned all your scouts here for an ascension,</p><p>but you left out the best part.</p><p>A conclave.</p><p>A final conclave.</p><p>One champion per clan.</p><p>One death instead of thousands.</p><p>And whoever wins gets the bunker.</p><p>Will you fight, or will you burn?</p><p>Remember, it&#39;s not black rain, but it can turn at any moment.</p><p>So keep the person with your assigned chem tent</p><p>in sight at all times.</p><p>&quot;No one but us saves ourselves.</p><p>We ourselves must walk the path.&quot;</p><p>Not too late to change your mind.</p><p>Yes, it is.</p><p>You can still stay, you know?</p><p>I&#39;m not a quitter.</p><p>Thanks for understanding.</p><p>Where&#39;s Monty?</p><p>Unloading the rover.</p><p>We&#39;re leaving it behind for you, by the way.</p><p>He didn&#39;t say good-bye?</p><p>Take care of him for us, will you?</p><p>You know I will.</p><p>May we meet again.</p><p>We won&#39;t.</p><p>Whatever the hell you want.</p><p>♪♪ No more destination, no more pain ♪♪</p><p>♪♪ Well, he said one thing before I graduate ♪♪</p><p>Monty?</p><p>♪♪ &quot;Never let your fear decide your fate.&quot; ♪♪</p><p>Everyone left. What are you doing here?</p><p>♪♪ Fly, fly, baby, don&#39;t cry ♪♪</p><p>♪♪ No need to worry &#39;cause everybody will die ♪♪</p><p>I love you, Harper.</p><p>♪♪ Every day we just go, go... ♪♪</p><p>Change your mind?</p><p>No.</p><p>I&#39;m here in case you guys change yours.</p><p>Always the optimist.</p><p>I love that about you.</p><p>I&#39;m glad you stayed.</p><p>Don&#39;t be a buzzkill. All right?</p><p>♪♪ Unexplainable sightings in the sky ♪♪</p><p>♪♪ I hate to be the one to ruin the night ♪♪</p><p>All right. We&#39;ll bring this stuff to the lighthouse,</p><p>see what else we can find on the island.</p><p>You guys ready or what?</p><p>Sorry we&#39;re late. There&#39;s been some developments.</p><p>Not all good. They&#39;ve--</p><p>fill you in on the way.</p><p>Is this everything we need?</p><ul><li>Yeah.</li><li>Great. We got it.</li></ul><p>Go get Raven.</p><p>Don&#39;t have much time.</p><p>Mass fiery death in 5 days.</p><p>Raven.</p><p>Little busy here.</p><p>Yeah, well, whatever&#39;s not packed,</p><p>you need to leave it.</p><p>It&#39;s time to go.</p><p>I&#39;m not going.</p><p>What the hell are you talking about?</p><p>I&#39;m dying, Murphy.</p><p>Come on. Abby said if you didn&#39;t use your brain, we--</p><p>we&#39;re past that now.</p><p>You&#39;re going to space?</p><p>Have any idea what it feels like</p><p>to be in pain every day?</p><p>When I was spacewalking,</p><p>everything was right.</p><p>I just want that again.</p><p>I&#39;m sorry.</p><p>I&#39;m sorry for doing this to you, Raven.</p><p>This is not your fault, Murphy.</p><p>I could deal with losing my leg,</p><p>but...Losing my mind...</p><p>What do you want me to tell the others?</p><p>Tell them...</p><p>Tell them I floated myself.</p><p>Go. Survive. Heh.</p><p>It&#39;s what cockroaches do, right?</p><p>Can we please get back to work?</p><p>Yeah. Yeah, OK, sorry.</p><p>Right. Where were we?</p><p>The entire city is the battlefield.</p><p>No time limit. No guns.</p><p>One warrior from each clan fights</p><p>until only one remains.</p><p>And the winner&#39;s clan takes the bunker.</p><p>Just like that.</p><p>Without guns</p><p>and without anyone trained in grounder combat,</p><p>there&#39;s no way we can win.</p><p>Hey, we fight or we die.</p><p>I&#39;m here for the war.</p>",615),a={render:function(e,p){return o}}}}]);